Not every Fourth feels like fireworks. But it can still mean something.
A low-key day at home: yard work, Hamilton, and sweaty porch sitting feels just right this year.
Because yeah, the world feels heavy… but we’ve still got little humans asking us to refill the water table and open the cheese sticks.
Here’s to the quiet versions of freedom. The messy, honest kind.

My clients asked if they should break their necks to get their house listed before the school year starts. I said absolutely not.
“But Jess, shouldn’t you ABC? Always be closing?” Nah, because I care about my clients. Not imaginary, hypothetical buyers.
These folks have two little kids, two geriatric dogs, two full-time jobs, and are building a house in another state.

Why would we rush that chaos?

Naps, bedtimes, dinner, moving dogs out for showings - that is not fun. I have clients doing it now. Ask them. It’s a nightmare.

This is why my clients trust me. Because I work for them and keep their real lives in mind. 
If you’re tired of real estate that feels like pressure and panic, I’m your gal. Let’s do it right.

I’m not your 2am realtor. 

I’m the “handle the hard stuff so you can sleep through the night” kind of realtor.

I help kind, busy people sell their homes without losing their minds or their values.

If your camera roll is 1,000 pictures of your kids and not a single one of your spouse because you’re too busy keeping a toddler from launching off the back of the couch… You’re my people.

I’ll give it to you straight, keep things moving, and make sure you’re never left wondering what the hell is happening in your own sale.

No cold calls. No cringe. Just a home sale that actually works - so you can get back to living your real life.

📍St. Louis / MO

📩 DM me “SELL” if you’re even thinking about it and want the no-BS roadmap.
